0class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20combustible%20fossils%E2%80%94petroleum%2C%20coal%2C%20and%20gas%E2%80%94are%20gifts%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fa-planetary-perspective%5C%22%3Ethe%20late%20Paleozoic%20era%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20trees%20grew%20and%20fell%20in%20heaps%2C%20when%20great%20blooms%20of%20plankton%20and%20algae%20sank%20under%20the%20silt%20of%20the%20seas.%20All%20their%20remains%2C%20collected%20together%20in%20mountainous%20quantities%20and%20pressed%20down%20over%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20years%2C%20encapsulate%20the%20stored%20energy%20of%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20years%20of%20sunlight%20that%20had%20fallen%20to%20Earth%20before%20the%20reign%20of%20the%20dinosaurs.%20That%20chemical%20potential%20had%20lain%20dormant%20in%20the%20belly%20of%20the%20Earth%2C%20taken%20out%20of%20circulation%20from%20the%20living%20systems%20on%20the%20surface%20of%20our%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20humans%20have%20resurrected%20that%20chemistry%20in%20a%20sudden%20burst.%20Its%20eruption%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20over%20the%20past%20three%20hundred%20years%E2%80%94a%20veritable%20explosion%20on%20geological%20timescales%E2%80%94cannot%20occur%20without%20also%20violently%20altering%20the%20biogeochemistry%20of%20our%20planet.%20This%20is%20the%20climate%20and%20ecological%20crisis%20we%20now%20live%20within.%20By%20several%20measures%2C%20the%20havoc%20it%E2%80%99s%20wrought%20leaves%20us%20at%20best%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fsep%2F13%2Fearth-well-outside-safe-operating-space-for-humanity-scientists-find%3FCMP%3DShare_iOSApp_Other%5C%22%3Eteetering%20on%20the%20brink%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20exceeding%20the%20ecological%20safety%20zone%20for%20humankind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20this%20glut%20of%20cheap%2C%20fossilised%20energy%20is%20limited%2C%20a%20one-time%20deal%20that%20can%20never%20be%20replicated%20in%20any%20human%20timeframe.%20Today%E2%80%99s%20oil%20will%20reach%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.e-education.psu.edu%2Femsc470%2Fnode%2F557%5C%22%3Eits%20own%20limit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20it%20simply%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2019%2F07%2F190711114846.htm%5C%22%3Etakes%20more%20energy%20to%20gather%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20fast%20enough%20to%20expand%20the%20economy%20than%20what%20it%20returns.%20Meanwhile%2C%20like%20an%20addict%2C%20the%20industrial%20economic%20beast%20is%20already%20desperately%20slurping%20up%20the%20lowest-quality%20dregs%20from%20so-called%20%3Cem%3Etight%20oil%3C%2Fem%3E%20sources%20(as%20opposed%20to%20%3Cem%3Econventional%20oil%3C%2Fem%3E%20sources).%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS2666049022000524%5C%22%3Edays%20of%20oil%20abundance%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjpt.spe.org%2Fplummeting-energy-return-on-investment-of-oil-and-the-impact-on-global-energy-landscape%5C%22%3Enumbered%20in%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F343768755_The_Resource-Limited_Plateau_in_Global_Conventional_Oil_Production_Analysis_and_Consequences%5C%22%3Enot%20decades%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Without%20cheap%20oil%20to%20help%20build%20and%20power%20mining%20operations%2C%20access%20to%20coal%20and%20gas%20would%20also%20be%20diminished%2C%20the%20necessary%20rate%20and%20scale%20rendered%20economically%E2%80%94if%20not%20also%20logistically%E2%80%94unfeasible%20using%20other%20power%20sources.%20Continuing%20to%20increase%20our%20dependency%20on%20these%20fossils%20in%20any%20way%20makes%20literally%20no%20Earthly%20sense.%20We%20must%20instead%20imagine%20a%20system%20that%20moves%20away%20from%20burning%20fossils%2C%20altogether%2C%20rap%C2%A0idly%20and%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20586px)%2085vw%2C%20586px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112734%2FCarbon-Budgets-2023.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22586%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112734%2FCarbon-Budgets-2023.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112734%2FCarbon-Budgets-2023-300x211.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112734%2FCarbon-Budgets-2023-1024x721.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700959%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22413%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20rate%20at%20which%20we%20must%20phase%20out%20fossil%20fuel%20sources%20and%20adjust%20land-use%20practices%20for%20a%2067%25%20chance%20of%20limiting%20global%20warming%20thresholds%20of%201.5%C2%BAC%20(green)%2C%201.7%C2%BAC%20(blue)%2C%20or%202.0%C2%BAC%20red.%20Chart%3A%20Friedlingstein%20et%20al%202023%20(https%3A%2F%2Fessd.copernicus.org%2Farticles%2F15%2F5301%2F2023%2Fessd-15-5301-2023.html)%3B%20Global%20Carbon%20Project%202023%20(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalcarbonproject.org%2Fcarbonbudget%2F)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20already%20built%20a%20world%20that%E2%80%99s%20now%20well%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3Estate%20of%20ecological%20overshoot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20locked%20into%20capitalism%E2%80%99s%20requirement%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fof-mice-and-men-energy-and-cancer%5C%22%3Egrowth%20in%20consumption%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20to%20keep%20the%20present%20system%20afloat%3A%20to%20keep%20the%20goods%20flowing%2C%20the%20steel%20and%20concrete%20rising%2C%20the%20institutions%20flush%20with%20resources%20for%20research%20and%20education%20and%20policymaking%2C%20the%20factories%20supplied%20with%20raw%20materials%20and%20industrial%20chemicals%E2%80%94many%20of%20which%20are%20directly%20sourced%20from%20petroleum.%20As%20a%20living%20system%20set%20upon%20a%20trajectory%20of%20unabated%20growth%2C%20our%20economy%20requires%20the%20massive%20overconsumption%20of%20both%20energy%20and%20materials%2C%20even%20as%20it%20destroys%20the%20living%20systems%20of%20the%20world%20upon%20which%20it%20depends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20crux%20of%20our%20predicament%3A%20Consumption%2C%20growth%2C%20socioeconomic%20wellbeing%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20inequalities%2C%20exploitation%2C%20pollution%2C%20species%20genocide%2C%20ecosystem%20annihilation%2C%20and%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20form%20a%20nexus%20of%20interdependencies%20that%20feed%20and%20perpetuate%20one%20another%20as%20the%20basis%20of%20modern%20global%20civilisation.%20This%20system%20is%20both%20unsustainable%20over%20time%20as%20well%20as%20immediately%20destructive%20for%20great%20multitudes%2C%20both%20human%20and%20non-human%2C%20even%20while%20we%20have%20made%20it%20foundational%20to%20the%20dreams%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20billions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20deployed%20thirsty%2C%20high-yielding%20strains%20of%20wheat%20and%20rice%20that%20grew%20well%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20artificial%20fertilisers%2C%20herbicides%2C%20and%20pesticides.%20As%20with%20any%20%E2%80%98progress%20trap%2C%E2%80%99%20the%20short-term%20benefits%20gained%20cannot%20overcome%20the%20long-term%20costs%20incurred%2C%20including%20soil%20destruction%3B%20groundwater%20depletion%3B%20chemical%20pollution%20of%20land%2C%20water%2C%20and%20people%3B%20loss%20of%20insects%20and%20other%20biodiversity%3B%20narrowing%20of%20the%20Indian%20diet%3B%20and%20extinction%20of%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fgrains-of-life-how-chotanagpurs-adivasis-are-reviving-native-varieties-of-rice%5C%22%3Eone%20lakh%20varieties%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20indigenous%20seeds%2C%20shrinking%20the%20available%20gene%20pool%20for%20food%20grains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20combustible%20fossil%20revolution%E2%80%94with%20a%20special%20emphasis%20on%20oil%E2%80%94absolutely%20underwrites%20the%20modern%20way%20of%20life.%20It%20has%20provided%20continuous%20growth%20in%20energy%20use%2C%20which%20%3Cem%3Ecannot%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20replicated%20by%20less%20concentrated%2C%20more%20unreliable%2C%20and%20seasonally%20or%20diurnally%20limited%20renewable%20sources.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20already%20know%20this.%20Why%20else%20would%20we%20Indians%20have%20argued%20for%20entitlements%20to%20burn%20more%20fossils%2C%20justified%20only%20by%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20rise%20to%20economic%20dominance%20by%20having%20done%20it%20first%3F%20If%20we%20believed%20%E2%80%98renewables%E2%80%99%20were%20a%20complete%20answer%2C%20we%20would%20gladly%20leapfrog%20the%20need%20for%20combustible%20fossils%20and%20build%20the%20great%20and%20%E2%80%98clean%E2%80%99%20Indian%20industrial%20economy.%20But%20despite%20all%20the%20%E2%80%98hope%E2%80%99%20elites%20declaim%20around%20%E2%80%98greening%E2%80%99%20our%20energy%20systems%2C%20we%20intuitively%20understand%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20way%20to%20have%20the%20%E2%80%98developed%2C%E2%80%99%20capitalist-consumerist%20economy%20without%20breaking%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20all%20the%20%E2%80%98renewable%E2%80%99%20energy%E2%80%94which%20is%20delivered%20to%20us%20only%20through%20installations%20that%20are%20%3Cem%3Enot%20at%20all%20renewable%3C%2Fem%3E%20but%20%3Cem%3Emust%20be%20built%20and%20re-built%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20every%20few%20decades%E2%80%94thus%20far%20deployed%20haven%E2%80%99t%20begun%20to%20reduce%20our%20fossil%20fuel%20consumption.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fourworldindata.org%2Fgrapher%2Felectricity-prod-source-stacked%5C%22%3Eonly%20added%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20our%20overall%20energy%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20581px)%2085vw%2C%20581px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22581%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution-300x212.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution-1024x723.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700960%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22410%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERenewable%20energy%20sources%20haven%E2%80%99t%20reduced%20our%20demand%20for%20combustible%20fossils.%20They%20have%20only%20allowed%20us%20to%20increase%20our%20overall%20energy%20consumption.%20Chart%3A%20Our%20World%20in%20Data%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20exposes%20the%20terrible%20reality%20that%20we%20%3Cem%3Ecannot%3C%2Fem%3E%20reduce%20our%20fossil%20fuel%20consumption%E2%80%94and%20associated%20carbon%20emissions%E2%80%94until%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jasonhickel.org%2Fblog%2F2023%2F11%2F24%2Fhow-popular-are-post-growth-and-post-capitalist-ideas%5C%22%3Estop%20growing%20the%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ending%20fossil-fuelled%20emissions%20means%20transitioning%20to%20a%20reduced%20energy-and-materials%20consumption%20economy.%20This%20requires%20simultaneously%20innovating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fd41586-022-04412-x%5C%22%3Ealternate%20modes%20of%20social%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20provisioning%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20allows%20other%20living%20systems%20also%20to%20flourish.%20It%20is%20the%20only%20viable%20path%20forward.%20This%20means%20prioritizing%20the%20uses%20of%20a%20limited%20energy%20budget%20in%20a%20way%20that%20equitably%20benefits%20the%20greatest%20number%20of%20people.%20And%20this%20implies%20austerity%20for%20the%20rich%E2%80%94indeed%2C%20a%20phase-out%20of%20wealth%20inequality%20and%20the%20mechanisms%20that%20create%20and%20maintain%20it.%20Taken%20together%2C%20this%20becomes%20an%20absolutely%20fundamental%20re-envisioning%20and%20restructuring%20of%20global%20society%20and%20the%20principles%20by%20which%20it%20functions%E2%80%94our%20social%20structures%2C%20value%20systems%2C%20identities%2C%20mythologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocieties%20do%20change%2C%20of%20course.%20They%20never%20stop%20changing%2C%20whether%20by%20consent%20or%20force%20of%20circumstance.%20For%20better%20or%20for%20worse.%20And%20that%20social%20change%20always%20entails%20an%20evolution%20in%20the%20stories%20we%20tell%20ourselves%2C%20for%20it%20is%20our%20stories%20that%20build%20the%20world%20we%20inhabit%E2%80%94as%20much%20as%20they%20can%20also%20blind%20us%20to%20other%20aspects%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20next%20essay%20will%20touch%20upon%20this%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0The%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Only%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710050720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112000%2FIMG_2968.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Four-insatiable-quest-for-fire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Continuing%20to%20increase%20our%20dependency%20on%20these%20fossils%20in%20any%20way%20makes%20literally%20no%20Earthly%20sen