ith-free-ott-tv-channels-and-more%2Farticleshow%2F108345923.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Economic%20Shocks%20like%20Note-Ban%2C%20GST%2C%20COVID%20Dragged%20Consumption%20Expenditure%20in%20the%20Last%20Decade%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F09115037%2Fimage-1929.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Demonetisation%2C%20goods%20and%20services%20tax%20(GST)%20implementation%2C%20and%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20have%20led%20to%20a%20slowdown%20in%20consumption%20expenditure%20growth%20in%20the%20previous%20decade%20as%20compared%20to%20the%20preceding%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20shocks%20have%20affected%20both%20rural%20and%20urban%20consumption%20patterns%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Feconomic-shocks-dragged-consumption-growth-in-previous-decade-nomura-124030800833_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20Nomura%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20on%20Friday%20(March%208).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELower%20compound%20annual%20growth%20rate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nomura%20analysis%2C%20based%20on%20the%20latest%20Household%20Consumption%20Expenditure%20Survey%2C%20shows%20a%20lower%20compound%20annual%20growth%20rate%20(CAGR)%20for%20rural%20and%20urban%20consumption%20compared%20to%20previous%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CReal%20rural%20consumption%20grew%20at%20a%20CAGR%20of%203.1%25%20during%202012-23%20(compared%20to%206.6%25%20in%202010-12)%2C%20while%20urban%20consumption%20slid%20to%202.6%25%20from%205.2%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20the%20report%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDuring%202005-10%2C%20rural%20and%20urban%20consumption%20in%20real%20terms%20grew%20at%204%25%20and%204.4%25%2C%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20we%20deflate%20expenditure%20by%20using%20suitable%20measures%20of%20inflation%2C%20we%20find%20a%20similar%20CAGR%20drop%20in%20real%20consumption%20expenditure%2C%20indicating%20that%20the%20fall%20is%20not%20an%20inflationary%20phenomenon.%20This%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20with%20the%20last%20decade%20witnessing%20shocks%20such%20as%20demonetisation%2C%20GST%20implementation%20and%20the%20pandemic%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDivergence%20in%20urban-rural%20consumption%20growth%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20nominal%20growth%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20(2012-2023)%20has%20been%20relatively%20more%20superlative%20for%20rural%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERural%20consumption%20has%20gone%20up%20by%20164%25%20during%202012-23%20period%20in%20comparison%20with%20around%20146%25%20for%20urban%20consumption%2C%20suggesting%20convergence%20in%20consumption%20levels.%20Earlier%2C%20between%202000-12%20period%2C%20rural%20consumption%20grew%20by%20194%25%20compared%20with%20207%25%20in%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20highlighted%20that%20inequality%20reduction%20in%20both%20rural%20and%20urban%20households%20has%20been%20driven%20by%20reductions%20in%20consumption%20among%20top%20spenders%20rather%20than%20increases%20among%20the%20bottom-most%20spenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20relatively%20better%20for%20urban%20India.%20%E2%80%9CRural%20India%20seems%20to%20be%20experiencing%20a%20%E2%80%98middle-class%20bulge%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20has%20seen%20maximum%20consumption%20growth%20among%20the%20consumer%20fractile%20classes%2C%20while%20growth%20has%20been%20much%20lower%20for%20the%20top%20spenders.%20The%20pattern%20is%20different%20for%20urban%20households%2C%20where%20the%20bottom%20consumption%20brackets%20have%20seen%20maximum%20consumption%20growth%2C%20which%20has%20progressively%20declined%20as%20we%20move%20into%20the%20higher%20brackets.%20This%20may%20be%20because%20the%20middle%20class%20in%20rural%20India%20seems%20to%20have%20benefited%20more%20from%20handouts%20than%20their%20urban%20counterparts%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanging%20consumer%20trends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20report%20highlighted%20the%20changing%20consumer%20tastes.%20The%20data%20on%20consumption%20patterns%20shows%20that%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Indian%20consumers%20are%20spending%20less%20on%20food%20and%20more%20on%20%E2%80%98core%E2%80%99%20(non-food%20and%20fuel)%20categories%20%E2%80%94%20more%20so%20in%20rural%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWithin%20the%20food%20categories%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20share%20of%20spending%20on%20beverages%20and%20processed%20food%20and%20fruits.%20These%20are%20typically%20indicative%20of%20more%20expensive%20and%20discerning%20consumer%20tastes.%20Within%20the%20core%20basket%2C%20consumers%20are%20mainly%20spending%20on%20conveyance%20and%20durable%20goods.%20The%20former%20suggests%20that%20consumers%20are%20increasingly%20becoming%20more%20mobile%20and%20also%20possibly%20that%20transportation%20costs%20have%20disproportionately%20picked%20up.%20The%20rise%20in%20durable%20goods%20consumption%20suggests%20that%20aspirational%20consumption%20has%20picked%20up%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20the%20report%20also%20noted%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20share%20of%20spending%20on%20intoxicants%20and%20toiletries%2C%20other%20household%20consumables%20and%20entertainment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CConsumers%20are%20%E2%80%98curiously%E2%80%99%20spending%20a%20lower%20share%20of%20their%20income%20on%20clothing%2C%20footwear%20and%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomic%20shocks%20impact%20consumption%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20reports%20highlighted%20how%20demonetisation%20had%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20small-%20and%20medium-sized%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20demonetisation%20accelerated%20digitalisation%20for%20many%20small%20industries%2C%20micro%20industries%20faced%20instability%2C%20Rajiv%20Chawla%2C%20president%20of%20Faridabad%20Small%20Industries%20Association%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fsmall-biz%2Fsme-sector%2Fdemonitisation-indian-smes-suffered-a-blow-still-struggling-to-find-their-footing%2Farticleshow%2F61541952.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehad%20told%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%202017.%20He%20said%20they%20lacked%20preparation%20and%20weren%E2%80%99t%20involved%20in%20the%20black%20economy.%20%E2%80%9CWorkers%20like%20dholwalas%2C%20dhaba%20owners%2C%20plumbers%2C%20and%20daily%20wage%20earners%20primarily%20dealt%20in%20cash%20and%20were%20unfamiliar%20with%20digital%20transactions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20while%20GST%20improved%20economic%20efficiency%2C%20critics%20say%20the%20complexities%20of%20the%20new%20regime%20have%20driven%20many%20small%20enterprises%20out%20of%20business%20and%20forced%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20out%20of%20jobs%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fgst-impact-powerlooms-panipat-jobs%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20survey%20by%20the%20All%20India%20Trade%20Union%20Congress%20(AITUC)%20in%20July%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fphotos%2Findia-news%2Fphotos-hundreds-of-thousands-laid-off-despite-post-gst-growth%2Fphoto-XpEj5sC31IJL7nWg3My1TN.html%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20fifth%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%2063%20million%20small%20businesses%20%E2%80%93%20contributing%2032%25%20to%20the%20economy%20and%20employing%20111%20million%20people%20%E2%80%93%20faced%20a%2020%25%20fall%20in%20profits%20since%20the%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0GST%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Erollout%2C%20and%20had%20to%20sack%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReadymade%20garments%2C%20gems%20and%20jewellery%2C%20leather%2C%20handicraft%20and%20basic%20machinery%20manufacturing%20are%20hit%20the%20most%2C%20industry%20bodies%20from%20across%20the%20country%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202020%2C%20just%20after%20the%20nationwide%20lockdown%20was%20announced%2C%20over%20122%20million%20people%20in%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fdata-over-12-crore-indians-lost-their-jobs-during-the-coronavirus-lockdown-in-april%2Farticle61660110.ece%5C%22%3Elost%20their%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20single%20month%2C%20the%20Hindu%20reported%20citing%20estimates%20from%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy.%20Around%2075%25%20of%20them%20were%20small%20traders%20and%20wage-labourers%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709969458000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F09115037%2Fimage-1929.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Feconomic-shocks-like-note-ban-gst-covid-dragged-consumption-expenditure-in-the-last-decade%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Real%20rural%20consumption%20grew%20at%20a%20CAGR%20of%203.1%25%20during%202012-23%20as%20compared%20to%206.6%25%20in%202010-12%2C%20while%20urban%20consumption%20slid%20to%202.6%25%20from%205.2%25%2C%20said%20Nomura%20in%20its%20report.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Feconomic-shocks-like-note-ban-gst-covid-dragged-consumption-expenditure-in-the-last-decade%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ex-Civil%20Servants%20Urge%20ECI%20to%20Prod%20SBI%20to%20Furnish%20Info%20on%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Before%20Lok%20Sabha%20Polls%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F05141137%2FState-Bank-of-India.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EAs%20many%20as%2079%20former%20civil%20servants%2C%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20Constitutional%20Conduct%20Group%20(CCG)%2C%20have%20written%20to%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20to%20direct%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20immediately%20release%20the%20details%20of%20donors%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20recently%20struck%20down%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%204%2C%20the%20SBI%20urged%20the%20court%20to%20extend%20the%20time%20for%20collating%20donors%E2%80%99%20data%20until%20June%2030%2C%20instead%20of%20earlier%20deadline%20of%20March%206.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20denying%20this%20information%20and%20indicating%20that%20it%20would%20not%20be%20available%20before%20the%20general%20elections%20seems%20to%20indicate%20that%20the%20SBI%20is%20shielding%20the%20Government%20in%20power%20from%20any%20criticism%20that%20there%20was%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20between%20the%20bonds%20and%20favours%20given%20to%20some%3Cbr%3E%5Cnfirms%20or%20raids%2Fintimidation%20to%20pressurize%20the%20corporates%20to%20fall%20in%20line%2C%E2%80%9D%20CCG%20said%20in%20its%20letter%20to%20ECI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublished%20below%20is%20the%20full%20statement%20and%20list%20of%20signatories%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECCG%20OPEN%20LETTER%20TO%20THE%20ELECTION%20COMMISSION%20OF%20INDIA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E9%20March%202024%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShri%20Rajiv%20Kumar%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EChief%20Election%20Commissioner%20Shri%20Arun%20Goel%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EElection%20Commissioner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDear%20Shri%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20and%20Shri%20Arun%20Goel%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20a%20group%20of%20former%20civil%20servants%20of%20the%20All%20India%20and%20Central%20Services%20who%20have%20worked%20in%20the%20Central%20and%20State%20Governments%20during%20our%20careers.%20As%20a%20group%2C%20we%20have%20no%20affiliation%20with%20any%20political%20party%20but%20believe%20in%20impartiality%2C%20neutrality%20and%20commitment%20to%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20writing%20to%20you%20with%20reference%20to%20the%20extraordinary%20request%20of%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20(SCI)%20to%20extend%20the%20time%20to%20submit%20information%20regarding%20electoral%20bonds%20till%20June%2030%2C%202024%2C%20by%20which%20time%20the%20elections%20to%20Parliament%20would%20be%20over.%20We%20note%20with%20dismay%20that%20it%20took%20SBI%20seventeen%20days%20to%20inform%20the%20Court%20on%204%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20March%20that%20they%20are%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20collate%20the%20data%20by%206%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20March.%20For%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20bank%20with%2048%20crore%20accounts%20and%20boasting%20high%20levels%20of%20digitization%2C%20a%20pathetic%20excuse%20has%20been%20proffered%20that%20records%20were%20kept%20manually%20and%20hence%20the%20extension%20sought.%20Thomas%20Franco%2C%20former%20General%20Secretary%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Banking%20Officers%20Confederation%2C%20has%20pointed%20out%20that%20SBI%20had%20asked%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20by%20a%20letter%20of%20June%202018%20for%20a%20sum%20of%20more%20than%20Rs%2060%20lakhs%20for%20development%20of%20IT%20systems%20for%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20In%20the%20same%20piece%2C%20Franco%20has%20also%20published%20an%20RTI%20reply%20that%20gives%2C%20in%20just%20a%20period%20of%20six%20days%2C%20details%20of%20bonds%20sold%20over%20six%20years.%20Subhash%20Chandra%20Garg%2C%20Finance%20Secretary%20at%20the%20time%20of%20finalization%20of%20the%20scheme%20(and%20a%20defender%20of%20it)%2C%20has%20said%20in%20interviews%20that%20it%20should%20not%20take%20more%20than%20ten%20minutes%20to%20get%20the%20information%20sought.%20He%20also%20makes%20the%20important%20point%20that%20the%20SCI%20has%20not%20asked%20for%20details%20linking%20the%20purchase%20of%20bonds%20with%20the%20political%20parties%20to%20whom%20they%20have%20been%20given%3B%20so%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20time%20is%20wholly%20unjustified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20striking%20down%20the%20scheme%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20as%20unconstitutional%2C%20the%20SCI%20had%20flagged%20both%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20citizens%20of%20India%20to%20know%20about%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%20and%20how%20there%20would%20be%20no%20level%20playing%20field%20if%20one%20party%20got%20undue%20financial%20advantage.%20The%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20denying%20this%20information%20and%20indicating%20that%20it%20would%20not%20be%20available%20before%20the%20general%20elections%20seems%20to%20indicate%20that%20the%20SBI%20is%20shielding%20the%20Government%20in%20power%20from%20any%20criticism%20that%20there%20was%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20between%20the%20bonds%20and%20favours%20given%20to%20some%20firms%20or%20raids%2Fintimidation%20to%20pressurize%20the%20corporates%20to%20fall%20in%20line.%20The%20media%20portals%20Newslaundry%20and%20News%20Minute%20have%20already%20published%20material%20linking%20thirty%20corporates%20and%20their%20purchase%20of%20bonds%20worth%20about%20Rs%20335%20crore%20in%20the%20previous%20five%20years%20to%20the%20blatant%20misuse%20of%20enforcement%20agencies%20to%20make%20these%20corporates%20fall%20in%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20would%20like%20to%20reference%20the%20letter%20of%20March%206%2C%202024%2C%20written%20by%20EAS%20Sarma%2C%20a%20former%20Secretary%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20in%20which%20he%20has%20requested%20the%20ECI%20not%20only%20to%20freeze%20any%20unspent%20funds%20of%20political%20parties%20from%20the%20scheme%20but%20also%20not%20to%20publish%20the%20schedule%20of%20elections%20till%20the%20SBI%20gives%20the%20information%20ordered%20by%20the%20SCI.%20We%20note%20that%20the%20term%20of%20the%20present%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20up%20to%20June%2016%2C%202024%2C%20and%20to%20complete%20the%20election%20in%20time%2C%20the%20ECI%20could%20announce%20the%20schedule%20by%20March%2027%2C%20or%20even%20earlier.%20The%20SBI%20should%20give%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20data%20much%20before%20the%20announcement%20of%20the%20elections.%20This%20is%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20ECI%20to%20reclaim%20its%20reputation%20and%20its%20integrity%20by%20using%20its%20powers%20under%20Article%20324%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20As%20Shri%20Sarma%20has%20suggested%2C%20it%20should%20direct%20the%20SBI%20to%20immediately%20release%20the%20information.%20The%20ECI%20should%20also%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20it%20will%20not%20announce%20the%20schedule%20for%20the%202024%20general%20elections%20till%20the%20SBI%20furnishes%20this%20information.%20If%20the%20ECI%20remains%20quiescent%2C%20it%20will%20not%20live%20up%20to%20its%20Constitutional%20mandate%20of%20respecting%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20Indian%20voters%20and%20of%20holding%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20on%20a%20level%20playing%20field.%20That%20would%20be%20a%20death%20blow%20for%20democracy%20in%20India%20as%20we%20know%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESATYAMEVA%20JAYATE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYours%20faithfully%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstitutional%20Conduct%20Group%20(%3C%2Fstrong%3E79%20signatories%2C%20as%20below)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2256%5C%22%3E1.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22111%5C%22%3EAnita%20Agnihotri%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2291%5C%22%3EIAS%20(Retd.)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22365%5C%22%3EFormer%20Secretary%2C%20Department%2